10.	what are distro-less images In docker?
A. Distroless images contain only your application and it's runtime dependencies with a very minimum operating system
libraries. They do not contain package managers, shell or any other programs you would expect to find in standard Linux 
distribution. They are very small and lightweight images.

11.	real-time challenges faced with docker? 
A. - Docker is a single Daemon process. Which can cause a single point of failure, If the docker Daemon goes down for
some reason all the applications are down.

-Docker Daemon runs as root user. Which is security threat. Any processing running as a root can have adverse
effect. When it is comprised for security reasons, it can impact other applications or container on the host.

-Resource containers: If you are running too many containers on a single host, you may experience issues with resource
constraints.  This can result in slow performance or crashes.

12.	what steps would you take to secure the container?
A. Some of the steps are:-
i) Use Distroless or images with not too many packages as your final image in multi stage build, So that there is
less chance of CVE or security issues.

ii) Ensure that the networking is configured properly. This is one of the most common reasons for security issues.
If required configure custom bridge networks and assigns them to isolate containers.

iii) Use utilities like sync to scan your container images.
